            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1371209446,
            "creation_date": 1371209446,
            "body": "<p>Please see the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-6.html#jls-6.4.1\" rel=\"noreferrer\">JLS<\/a><\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>6.4.2. Obscuring<\/p>\n<p>A simple name may occur in contexts where it may potentially be interpreted as the name of a variable, a type, or a package. In these situations, the rules of §6.5 specify that a variable will be chosen in preference to a type, and that a type will be chosen in preference to a package. Thus, it is may sometimes be impossible to refer to a visible type or package declaration via its simple name. We say that such a declaration is obscured.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>Under section <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-6.html#jls-6.5.2\" rel=\"noreferrer\">6.5.2. Reclassification of Contextually Ambiguous Names<\/a>:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If the name to the left of the &quot;.&quot; is reclassified as a TypeName, then:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>If the Identifier is the name of a method or field of the type denoted by TypeName, this AmbiguousName is reclassified as an ExpressionName.<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li><p>Otherwise, if the Identifier is the name of a member type of the type denoted by TypeName, this AmbiguousName is reclassified as a TypeName.<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li><p>Otherwise, a compile-time error occurs.<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<\/blockquote>\n",
            "answer_id": 17107490,
            "question_id": 17107384,
            "last_edit_date": 1592644375
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/LRpou.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 482279,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 896588,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/896588/andr%c3%a9-stannek",
                "reputation": 7853,
                "display_name": "Andr&#233; Stannek",
                "accept_rate": 85
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1371209471,
            "creation_date": 1371209471,
            "body": "<p>Your inner class and static variable are named the same. It doesn't have to do anything with the order of class loading, <code>X.Y<\/code> is interpreted as an acces to the variable, not the inner class.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17107497,
            "question_id": 17107384
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/tNrYV.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 2222583,
